{"submission_id":"sub_e51d08eb21bb4a44","run_id":"2026-06-19T18-34-18-410Z_357538-46a1d33d_ingest_flatbush-ave-state-st-grand-army-plaza-street-design-checklist","submitted_at":"2026-06-19T18:40:06.128Z","tool_args_sha256":"sha256:e51d08eb21bb4a4441cda60d5082b538d47a1d45f94e13503d2f2f5357a64614","schema_version":2,"tool_args":{"source_id":"flatbush_ave_state_st_grand_army_plaza_street_design_checklist","observation_kind":"project","local_observation_id":"project_flatbush_ave_state_st_grand_army_plaza","create_new":true,"label":"Flatbush Avenue - State Street to Grand Army Plaza","raw_text":"Project Name: Flatbush Avenue - State Street to Grand Army Plaza - 1. ADA Accessibility: Included In Project 2. Bus Bulbs: Not Included In Project - NYC DOT is installing Center-Running Bus Boarding Islands. Bus Bulbs are more appropriate on offset bus lane project. The center-running nature of this project's bus lanes preclude bus bulbs 3. Bus Lanes: Included In Project 4. Daylighting: Included In Project 5. Dedicated Vehicle Loading and Unloading Zones: Included In Project 6. Narrow Vehicle Lanes (10ft or Less): Included In Project 7. Pedestrian Safety Islands: Included In Project 8. Protected Bicycle Lane: Not Included In Project -A Protected Bicycle Lane is not feasible/needed at this location at this time based on professional engineering judgment 9. Signal-Protected Pedestrian Crossings: Included In Project 10. Signal Retiming: Included In Project 11. Wide Sidewalks (8ft or Greater): Not Included In Project -Due to resource constraints, Sidewalk Widening will not occur at this time - NYC DOT is adding painted pedestrian curb extensions at several intersections as part of this project.","payload":{"project_name":"Flatbush Avenue - State Street to Grand Army Plaza","project_type":"Major Transportation Project","status":"pre-implementation","description":"Street design project on Flatbush Avenue from State Street to Grand Army Plaza, including bus lanes, daylighting, pedestria